parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Intermittent Engine Stalling and Auto Start/Stop Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent engine stalling and auto start/stop failure can cause the vehicle to unexpectedly shut down while driving or stopped, leading to a loss of control, accidents, or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls while driving or stopped
the vehicle shuts down and shifts into neutral
the auto start/stop feature fails to restart the engine
the dashboard goes blank or flashes
the vehicle requires multiple attempts to restart
the vehicle experiences a sudden loss of power
and warning lights may appear on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical system malfunction can cause the vehicle to experience a sudden loss of power, leading to a loss of control, accidents, or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences a sudden loss of power
the radio and other electrical systems malfunction
the heat/air buttons switch by themselves
the shift paddles malfunction
and the vehicle's electrical systems may shut down while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The auto braking system malfunction can cause the vehicle to unexpectedly brake or accelerate, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The auto braking system engages abruptly without necessity
the vehicle accelerates suddenly
and the system may malfunction in certain situations
such as when the sensors are dirty.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the auto-idle stop feature can cause the vehicle to stall or shift into neutral at a stop, making it difficult or impossible to accelerate, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or shifts into neutral at a stop
the engine shuts off and fails to restart
the vehicle requires restarting
the vehicle is stuck in neutral
and the driver is unable to accelerate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The poor resolution of the rear backup camera can cause the driver to not see obstacles or people behind the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The rear backup camera display is blurry
the camera resolution is poor
and the driver is unable to see obstacles or people behind the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the battery can cause the vehicle to stall or shut down, making it difficult or impossible to operate, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The battery fails
the vehicle shuts down
the vehicle stalls
and the driver is unable to operate the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The explosion of the sunroof can cause injuries or accidents, and can also lead to damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: The sunroof explodes
shatters
or breaks
and the driver or occupants are injured or at risk of injury.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the auto idle stop feature can cause the engine to stall or shut off unexpectedly, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially when stopping at intersections or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The engine stalls or shuts off when coming to a stop
the vehicle goes into neutral
the battery sign appears on the dashboard
the vehicle is unable to restart immediately
the vehicle takes a few minutes to restart.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Knocking or Loss of Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine knocking or loss of power can cause the engine to fail, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The engine knocks or makes a loud noise
the vehicle loses power
the vehicle is unable to accelerate
the vehicle stalls or shuts off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The clanking noise from the engine compartment can indicate a serious engine problem, which can lead to engine failure and increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: A clanking noise emanates from the engine compartment
the noise is audible when starting the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the Auto Start/Stop system can cause the vehicle to stall or shift into neutral unexpectedly, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or shifts into neutral when attempting to restart after an auto stop
the brake pedal feels spongy
the parking light
brake system light
oil pressure light
and battery light may be illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration and deceleration can cause loss of control, accidents, and near-misses, especially when driving at low speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly without pressing the gas pedal
decelerates unexpectedly when stepping on the gas pedal
hesitates when accelerating
slips into neutral
and may experience back rolling or sudden acceleration from a standstill.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission and braking system issues can cause loss of control, accidents, and near-misses, especially when driving on inclines or at low speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates when accelerating
rolls backward on an incline
lurches forward when pressing the gas pedal
and may experience unusual humming noises or vibrations.
